To install the RXTX package (enables use of serial/parallel port hardware
with Java), simply untar the "rxtx-install_files.tar.gz" in the top level
java directory. 

If java is located in /usr/java/j2sdk/ and "rxtx-install_files.tar.gz"
is in /root/, perform the following:

cd /usr/java/j2sdk/
tar -xvzf /root/rxtx-install_files.tar.gz

This should install RXTX version 2.1-7pre17 by decompressing:
jre/lib/ext/RXTXcomm.jar
lib/ext/comm.jar
lib/javax.comm.properties
jre/lib/i386/librxtxI2C.so
jre/lib/i386/librxtxParallel.so
jre/lib/i386/librxtxRS485.so
jre/lib/i386/librxtxRaw.so
jre/lib/i386/librxtxSerial.so

To access the packages from your java source code, put "import gnu.io.*;"
at the top of your class.
